pullRequest.body:
Following on from #10097, which converted the companion of a quadratic form with a bilinear map, this PR replaces a number of results about quadratic forms and bilinear forms with results about quadratic forms and scalar valued bilinear maps. The long term aim is to be able to consider quadratic maps.

The main change is to `LinearAlgebra/QuadraticForm/Basic`, but this necessitates changes throughout `LinearAlgebra/QuadraticForm/`. Minor changes are also required elsewhere:

- `LinearAlgebra/CliffordAlgebra/`
- `LinearAlgebra/Matrix/PosDef`
- `LinearAlgebra/SesquilinearForm`
- A number of additional results about tensor products and linear maps are also required.

> I don't think we want to drop `BilinForm` as a name.

> I would prefer in the shorter term that we introduce `abbrev LinearMap.BilinForm`, and use that in place of the existing `BilinForm`. That gives us a nice namespace to put all the results abut bilinear maps in.

This is not what is been done in other files about bilinear maps (in particular `LinearAlgebra/BilinearMap` and `LinearAlgebra/SesquilinearForm`). Everything is in `LinearMap` to allow for dot-notation.

Dot notation works just fine with an `abbrev` too, and I think it makes things more readable to distinguish linear maps from bilinear forms, for the same reason as we distinguish LinearMap from Module.Dual.

I don't think we want to drop `BilinForm` as a name.

I would prefer in the shorter term that we introduce `abbrev LinearMap.BilinForm`, and use that in place of the existing `BilinForm`. That gives us a nice namespace to put all the results abut bilinear maps in.
Can you prove one using the other, rather than copy-pasting the file?
I still think we should get rid of `BilinForm` and tangling the replacement to the deprecated definition only makes everything worse.
In this case, I'm suggesting we reprove the `BilinForm` case in terms of the `LinearMap` case; indeed we don't want things to depend on the deprecated definition.
(I agree in the long term `structure BilinForm` should not exist)

@eric-wieser To define `BilinForm.tensorDistrib` in terms of `LinearMap.tensorDistrib` I think we need a map:
```
BilinForm A M₁ ⊗[R] BilinForm R M₂ →ₗ[A] (M₁ →ₗ[A] M₁ →ₗ[A] A) ⊗[R] (M₂ →ₗ[R] M₂ →ₗ[R] R)
```
This is okay:
```
#check TensorProduct.map ((toLin (R₂ := R) (M₂ := M₁)).toLinearMap) ((toLin (R₂ := R) (M₂ := M₂)).toLinearMap)
```
But `TensorProduct.lift` is not hetrobasic, so this fails:
```
#check TensorProduct.map ((toLin (R₂ := A) (M₂ := M₁)).toLinearMap) ((toLin (R₂ := R) (M₂ := M₂)).toLinearMap)
```
I'm pretty sure the current definition of `BilinForm.tensorDistrib` already contains the new definition as a subexpression?

Ah!
```
#check TensorProduct.AlgebraTensorModule.congr ((toLin (R₂ := A) (M₂ := M₁))) (toLin (R₂ := R) (M₂ := M₂)) 
```
Thanks.

So, something like this?
```
def tensorDistrib : BilinForm A M₁ ⊗[R] BilinForm R M₂ →ₗ[A] BilinForm A (M₁ ⊗[R] M₂) :=
  LinearMap.toBilin.toLinearMap ∘ₗ (LinearMap.tensorDistrib R A ∘ₗ 
    (TensorProduct.AlgebraTensorModule.congr toLin toLin ).toLinearMap)
```
Yes, that looks good to me

I'd argue this should be
```suggestion
Copyright (c) 2023 Eric Wieser. All rights reserved.
Released under Apache 2.0 license as described in the file LICENSE.
Authors: Eric Wieser, Christopher Hoskin
```
since I think this is largely copied from the other file.
Fair enough!
If we're claiming that `BilinForm` is the soon-to-be-deprecated version, then I think this comment belongs in `LinearAlgebra.BilinearForm.TensorProduct` pointing in the other direction.
Done.

```suggestion
theorem baseChange₂_tmul (B₂ : M₂ →ₗ[R] M₂ →ₗ[R] R) (a : A) (m₂ : M₂)
```
Can you use this to prove the other `IsSymm.tmul`?

I started looking at this. The BilinForm version of `IsSymm` doesn't require the semiring to be commutative. To do this properly I think we'd want the second argument to be a right module over `R` instead of a left module. Alternatively we could pursue the same strategy as we did with quadratic forms and remove the non-commutative semi-ring case for now.

#10422
Turns out I was wrong - it is possible to prove `BilinForm.IsSymm.tmul` using `LinearMap.IsSymm.tmul` without changing the definition of `BilinForm.IsSymm`. I've pushed a commit to that effect.
You should be able to do something similar to `tensorDistribEquiv` below too.
Yes, I was just working on that. Done.
This simp is now non-terminal, which isn't a good thing
Oops. Fixed.

I don't think this is good style: if the conclusion is broken across multiple lines, then the proof should get its own line; that is
```lean
example :
    something = something := rfl
```
is fine, as is
```lean
example :
    something = something :=
  rfl
```
but
```lean
example :
    something
      = something := rfl
```
is not, as it is much harder to see where the statement ends
Thanks. I've put this back to rfl.
If something can be proved with `rfl`, it is usually best not to try and prove it with a different lemma; only `rfl` makes this eligible for `dsimp`.
Put back to rfl.
idem
Put back to rfl.
Should this say "bilinear forms"? I think everything in this file is about `M₂ →ₗ[R] M₂ →ₗ[R] R`
I've now removed this file as suggested below.

I'm now leaning torwards merging #10632 first; with that in place, I think we can just update `LinearAlgebra/BilinearForm/TensorProduct.lean` in place, rather than copying it. I don't think after this PR there is any need to keep content on tensor products of `_root_.BilinForm`.
Okay, I've merged in `master` with #10632, have deleted `LinearAlgebra/TensorProduct/LinearMap` and have updated  `LinearAlgebra/BilinearForm/TensorProduct`.
Even before we decide about #10632; does anything use this file any more? If not, I'd be tempted to just delete it now.
I've put the `LinearMap.BilinForm` versions of these results in this file instead, as suggested above.

In this interest of keeping this PR small, I'd be inclined to use `BilinForm R M` here (the abbreviation), even though in a future PR I know you want to replace it with `M →ₗ[R] M →ₗ[R] N`. Is that OK with you?

Okay, I've changed it. I wasn't sure if I should be replacing every occurrence of `M →ₗ[R] M →ₗ[R] R` with `LinearMap.BilinForm` or just the ones where we want to use the dot notation.

In future should we have `protected abbrev BilinMap : Type _ := M →ₗ[R] M →ₗ[R] N`?
This diff would go away if you used `open LinearMap (BilinForm)` at the top of the file.
I think we should rename this back to `polarBilin` now.
Done.
@eric-wieser Should I put this back to `(LinearMap.)BilinForm R M`?
Yes please
@eric-wieser okay, I think I've done that everywhere now. Thanks.
